modules.description: Provides functions for parsing, formatting, and manipulating date-time values, including timezone conversions and duration calculations. Operates on custom date-time records and time intervals represented as integers. Used to generate human-readable timestamps and compute time differences in logging and scheduling systems.

Provides functions to retrieve the local time zone name and associated identifiers. Operates on time zone data structures specific to the system's configuration. Used to dynamically obtain time zone information for logging or localization purposes.
